    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is the phase II, single-arm, single-center study assessing the efficacy of weekly
      docetaxel plus carboplatin in second-line treatment of malignant melanoma (unresectable or
      metastatic) who has failed dacarbazine or temozolomide contained therapy. The primary end
      point is overall response rate according to RECIST 1.1 criteria assessed using CT or MRI and
      secondary end point includes disease control rate, progression free survival, overall
      survival and safety.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
